lg.l:
Like the
                                                  doves voice, like transient day. like music in the
                                                  air;

For thou
                                                  shalt be clothed in light, and fed with morning
                                                  manna;

But Thel
                                                  is like a faint cloud kindled at the rising
                                                  sun;

Why thou
                                                  complainest not when in one hour thou fade
                                                  away;

And court
                                                  the fair eyed dew. to take me to her shining
                                                  tent;

Dost thou
                                                  O little Cloud? I fear that I am not like
                                                  thee;

Ah weep
                                                  not little voice, thou can'st not speak. but thou
                                                  can'st weep;

The Clod
                                                  of Clay heard the Worms voice, & raisd her
                                                  pitying head;

Thou
                                                  seest me the meanest thing. and so I am
                                                  indeed;
